## Additional Decisions Documented

### Two `seed.py` files — Keep Both

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `server/seed.py` | Thin CLI entry point — `python seed.py` |
| `server/app/seeder/seed.py` | Full data generation logic (897 lines) |
| `server/app/seeder/__init__.py` | Flask CLI adapter — `flask seed --fresh` |

Both entry points call the same `run_seed()`. Keeping both for developer convenience.

### Stale Migrations — Deleted

All 3 files in `migrations/versions/` built against the old 14-table schema were deleted. A fresh migration will be generated with `flask db migrate -m "Initial 19-table schema"` when PostgreSQL setup is executed.

### BulkDeposit vs `/sessions/bulk` — Clarified

| | `POST /sessions/bulk` | `POST /bulk-deposits` |
|---|---|---|
| Creates | `RecyclingSession` + `RecyclingItem[]` | `BulkDeposit` (single record) |
| Simulates | RVM machine session with ML items | Admin manually crediting points (no machine) |
| Required fields | `rvmId`, `items[]` with `detectedClass` | `walletId`, `totalPointsAwarded`, `itemCount` |
| Points flow | Wallet ← Session total | Wallet ← Bulk deposit total |
| Transaction tag | `reference_type='recycling_session'` | `reference_type='bulk_deposit'` |

Both credit the same `Wallet.points_balance`. The `BulkDeposit` table provides audit trail for who approved a manual credit, how many items, and why — separate from the machine-based transaction ledger.

